HEADWORD: Arthrostraca
<hw>Ar*thros"tra*ca</hw>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'a`rqron</grk> joint + <?/ a shell.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the larger divisions of Crustacea, so called because the
thorax and abdomen are both segmented; Tetradecapoda. It includes the
Amphipoda and Isopoda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

